Enough of this bullshit.

244
00:12:21.324 --> 00:12:24.326
You need to go back
to New Jersey now.

245
00:12:24.327 --> 00:12:27.581
And you need to pay
for what you've done.

246
00:12:29.332 --> 00:12:33.378
So. maybe <i>you</i> need
to leave town.

247
00:12:38.467 --> 00:12:39.884
Fair warning.

248
00:13:02.240 --> 00:13:06.160
<i>♪ So long ♪</i>

249
00:13:06.161 --> 00:13:12.834
<i>♪ Hope we'll meet
again Someday ♪</i>

250
00:13:13.877 --> 00:13:18.173
<i>♪ Hope that maybe
then You'll say ♪</i>

251
00:13:20.926 --> 00:13:27.598
<i>♪ "Darling. I was wrong" ♪</i>

252
00:13:27.599 --> 00:13:29.600
Missed you. man.

253
00:13:29.601 --> 00:13:32.186
I know.

254
00:13:32.187 --> 00:13:35.856
I stopped selling heroin.

255
00:13:35.857 --> 00:13:38.192
What? You did that for me?

256
00:13:38.193 --> 00:13:42.029
I didn't wanna poison
the community no more.

257
00:13:42.030 --> 00:13:46.033
But you're still
selling women's bodies.

258
00:13:46.034 --> 00:13:48.619
gambling. and loan sharking.

259
00:13:48.620 --> 00:13:50.579
I'm trying my best.

260
00:13:50.580 --> 00:13:52.831
What I gotta do to
get your approval?

261
00:13:52.832 --> 00:13:55.459
You had your time with me.

262
00:13:55.460 --> 00:14:00.047
I'm lost. I need your help.

263
00:14:00.048 --> 00:14:03.175
Every man has to find his way.

264
00:14:03.176 --> 00:14:06.595
I planted the seeds.

265
00:14:06.596 --> 00:14:09.014
I gave you my friendship.

266
00:14:09.015 --> 00:14:11.893
Whatever wisdom I had. but
I can't tell you what to do.

267
00:14:15.730 --> 00:14:18.315
You have to make choices.

268
00:14:18.316 --> 00:14:20.818
You planted the seeds in Elise.

269
00:14:20.819 --> 00:14:23.029
Now she's a Black Panther.

270
00:14:24.281 --> 00:14:26.782
It's got me scared.

271
00:14:26.783 --> 00:14:32.121
Elise has a fortitude that
you can't even imagine.

272
00:14:35.917 --> 00:14:38.836
She got that from you.

273
00:14:41.047 --> 00:14:42.923
It's real.

274
00:14:45.093 --> 00:14:46.302
You're real.

275
00:14:46.303 --> 00:14:49.305
You're here.

276
00:14:49.306 --> 00:14:52.391
I'm in you.

277
00:15:00.066 --> 00:15:01.693
- Hey.
- Hey.

278
00:15:18.960 --> 00:15:24.089
Bacon smells <i>good</i>
today. Miss Green.

279
00:15:24.090 --> 00:15:26.175
Extra crispy with eggs over easy

280
00:15:26.176 --> 00:15:28.052
coming right up. and
two sides of grits.

281
00:15:28.053 --> 00:15:31.138
You are a saint that
serves. Hey. how's your boy?

282
00:15:31.139 --> 00:15:33.140
Still getting bigger
by the minute?

283
00:15:33.141 --> 00:15:34.350
Can't stop it.
Wouldn't if I could.

284
00:15:34.351 --> 00:15:38.313
Say now. don't let
him work you too hard.

285
00:15:45.111 --> 00:15:46.987
- Psst.
- Lord Jesus.

286
00:15:46.988 --> 00:15:48.489
Relax. It's me.

287
00:15:48.490 --> 00:15:50.157
They come here every day?

288
00:15:50.158 --> 00:15:52.743
Who. the fuzz?

289
00:15:52.744 --> 00:15:55.162
Without fail. Eating
for free every day.

290
00:15:55.163 --> 00:15:57.748
Every day. same
time. same shift?

291
00:15:57.749 --> 00:15:59.124
Last I checked. you
wasn't no reporter.

292
00:15:59.125 --> 00:16:02.211
so what's this really about?

293
00:16:02.212 --> 00:16:04.546
They think they're invincible.

294
00:16:04.547 --> 00:16:06.840
but they're flesh and
blood. like the rest of us.

295
00:16:06.841 --> 00:16:09.051
Think they could use
a reminder of that.

296
00:16:09.052 --> 00:16:11.053
You get blue blood
on your hands.

297
00:16:11.054 --> 00:16:12.721
you might not live
to wash it off.

298
00:16:12.722 --> 00:16:14.348
It would break your
father's heart.

299
00:16:14.349 --> 00:16:17.309
My father was good
friends with Malcolm X.

300
00:16:17.310 --> 00:16:18.769
the very man who taught me

301
00:16:18.770 --> 00:16:21.647
to yank the white
man's foot off my neck.

302
00:16:21.648 --> 00:16:23.982
The moment I decide
to carry my own rifle.

303
00:16:23.983 --> 00:16:26.151
my father wants me to sit down
and stay in a woman's place.

304
00:16:26.152 --> 00:16:28.237
Bumpy buried Malcolm.

305
00:16:28.238 --> 00:16:30.239
If he had to bury you.
it would kill him.

306
00:16:30.240 --> 00:16:32.241
Thought about that?

307
00:16:32.242 --> 00:16:37.955
Malcolm put his ideals
above his own life.

308
00:16:37.956 --> 00:16:39.373
How can I do any different?

309
00:17:03.314 --> 00:17:05.065
You smoking now?

310
00:17:05.066 --> 00:17:09.778
I'm nervous. okay? I'm upset.

311
00:17:09.779 --> 00:17:14.241
All right. Just try not
to blow it in my face.

312
00:17:14.242 --> 00:17:15.993
Please.

313
00:17:21.249 --> 00:17:24.084
- Sorry.
- It's all right.

314
00:17:24.085 --> 00:17:26.253
Maybe what we need
to do is pray.

315
00:17:26.254 --> 00:17:29.173
I don't believe in
prayer. Miss Willa.

316
00:17:29.174 --> 00:17:33.594
Bumpy's in the hospital.
Colombo has Chance.

317
00:17:33.595 --> 00:17:35.679
And you not gonna pray for them?

318
00:17:35.680 --> 00:17:37.389
No. I'm not.

319
00:17:37.390 --> 00:17:39.349
I'm not gonna get my hopes up.

320
00:17:39.350 --> 00:17:41.268
Pray for something that
don't happen. I hate that.

321
00:17:41.269 --> 00:17:44.271
I tell you what. Let's
pray for you. too.

322
00:17:44.272 --> 00:17:47.274
'cause there's
something I do know.

323
00:17:47.275 --> 00:17:49.443
And that is God will hear me.

324
00:17:49.444 --> 00:17:52.488
and he will take care of Bumpy.

325
00:17:52.489 --> 00:17:54.073
This I know.

326
00:17:55.742 --> 00:18:02.331
Lord. I'm asking for some grace.

327
00:18:02.332 --> 00:18:06.293
And I'm asking you to take
care of Bumpy and Chance.

328
00:18:06.294 --> 00:18:08.462
Hold on. Lord.

329
00:18:08.463 --> 00:18:10.839
Are you gonna eavesdrop. or
are you gon' pray with me?

330
00:18:10.840 --> 00:18:13.425
You can't do this wrong.

331
00:18:13.426 --> 00:18:16.261
Just pray from your heart.
and God will listen to you

332
00:18:16.262 --> 00:18:19.306
'cause you're praying
for the ones you love.

333
00:18:19.307 --> 00:18:21.934
I love Bumpy...

334
00:18:21.935 --> 00:18:24.478
and Chance.

335
00:18:24.479 --> 00:18:26.313
Even though sometimes
he can be difficult

336
00:18:26.314 --> 00:18:28.106
and kind of mean at times.

337
00:18:28.107 --> 00:18:32.361
But I-I do love them.

338
00:18:32.362 --> 00:18:33.278
Perfect.

339
00:18:33.279 --> 00:18:35.531
Well. let's pray for 'em. then.

340
00:18:35.532 --> 00:18:37.158
Come on.

341
00:18:43.414 --> 00:18:44.916
Okay.

342
00:18:49.629 --> 00:18:51.798
Figured you was hungry.

343
00:18:55.969 --> 00:18:59.346
All dogs gotta eat. huh?

344
00:18:59.347 --> 00:19:01.266
Don't try nothing stupid.

345
00:19:09.023 --> 00:19:10.149
Go on. eat.

346
00:19:16.197 --> 00:19:17.573
Look at you.

347
00:19:17.574 --> 00:19:20.117
You ain't all high and mighty
now to work with whitey.

348
00:19:20.118 --> 00:19:23.370
begging Colombo like a
dog to save your skin.

349
00:19:23.371 --> 00:19:27.416
So. you best start putting
some respect on my name.

350
00:19:27.417 --> 00:19:31.295
Ask me. the moment
you get out that chair

351
00:19:31.296 --> 00:19:33.839
and you free.

352
00:19:33.840 --> 00:19:36.174
you gon' put a put a
bullet in Colombo head.

353
00:19:36.175 --> 00:19:38.176
Wrong.

354
00:19:38.177 --> 00:19:39.928
I'm-a put a bullet in yours.

355
00:19:39.929 --> 00:19:41.763
How about I go
tell Colombo that?

356
00:19:41.764 --> 00:19:44.641
He won't give a damn.
Don't you get that?

357
00:19:44.642 --> 00:19:46.560
He don't care about
us Black folk.

358
00:19:46.561 --> 00:19:48.437
Bumpy Johnson don't give
a fuck about me neither.

359
00:19:48.438 --> 00:19:50.981
Bumpy Johnson gave you a chance.

360
00:19:50.982 --> 00:19:53.358
<i>You</i> fucked it up.

361
00:19:53.359 --> 00:19:55.444
I mean. come on now. Be real.

362
00:19:55.445 --> 00:19:57.738
He expect me to
steal all that dope

363
00:19:57.739 --> 00:20:00.449
and not take none for myself?

364
00:20:00.450 --> 00:20:02.200
I mean. come on. Even
you smarter than that.

365
00:20:04.203 --> 00:20:06.164
The fuck is so funny?

366
00:20:07.832 --> 00:20:10.292
When I first came to Harlem.

367
00:20:10.293 --> 00:20:12.419
I was as lost and stupid as you.

368
00:20:12.420 --> 00:20:15.797
Ready to rob. steal.

369
00:20:15.798 --> 00:20:17.424
kill anybody that got in my way.

370
00:20:17.425 --> 00:20:19.052
You come out here to
seek your fortune?

371
00:20:24.474 --> 00:20:25.390
I'd just gotten out of the Army.

372
00:20:25.391 --> 00:20:29.478
503rd Battalion. Korea.

373
00:20:29.479 --> 00:20:31.813
All Black unit with
a white lieutenant

374
00:20:31.814 --> 00:20:34.399
who treated us
like cannon fodder.

375
00:20:34.400 --> 00:20:38.487
I was one of the
few who survived.

376
00:20:38.488 --> 00:20:41.531
They even gave me a Silver Star.

377
00:20:41.532 --> 00:20:44.493
I wore it proudly when I
got home to Mississippi...

378
00:20:44.494 --> 00:20:48.664
until a city marshal and
his boys beat me blind

379
00:20:48.665 --> 00:20:53.251
for jaywalking on
Howard Avenue in Biloxi.

380
00:20:53.252 --> 00:20:55.671
Threw my ass in jail.

381
00:20:55.672 --> 00:21:00.300
When I got out. came north.

382
00:21:00.301 --> 00:21:05.347
Everybody in Harlem said
Bumpy Johnson was the man.

383
00:21:05.348 --> 00:21:09.476
So. I asked him for a
job. He said. "Hell. no."

384
00:21:09.477 --> 00:21:12.854
He could see I'd become wild.

385
00:21:12.855 --> 00:21:18.026
disloyal to anybody or anything.

386
00:21:18.027 --> 00:21:19.862
That sound familiar?

387
00:21:22.532 --> 00:21:24.282
How you end up with him. then?

388
00:21:24.283 --> 00:21:28.495
He didn't give me no job.
He gave me a book to read...

389
00:21:28.496 --> 00:21:31.331
"Native Son." Richard Wright.

390
00:21:31.332 --> 00:21:32.666
Then he gave me another one.

391
00:21:32.667 --> 00:21:36.503
Slowly but surely.
he made me understand

392
00:21:36.504 --> 00:21:38.672
that I needed brains
more than fists.

393
00:21:38.673 --> 00:21:41.341
That's when he gave me a job.

394
00:21:41.342 --> 00:21:43.468
Small things at first.

395
00:21:43.469 --> 00:21:46.096
Running numbers and shit.

396
00:21:46.097 --> 00:21:47.681
Then bigger stuff.

397
00:21:47.682 --> 00:21:50.100
Bumpy gave me a big
job right off the bat.

398
00:21:50.101 --> 00:21:52.310
Maybe 'cause he saw
something in you.

399
00:21:52.311 --> 00:21:55.732
Maybe even... something great.

400
00:21:57.442 --> 00:21:59.109
Yeah. well. it's too late now.

401
00:21:59.110 --> 00:22:00.527
so fuck it.

402
00:22:00.528 --> 00:22:02.070
Hell. if he ain't
dead yet already.

403
00:22:02.071 --> 00:22:05.115
he ain't gon' give me
no second chance anyway.

404
00:22:05.116 --> 00:22:06.324
He would.

405
00:22:06.325 --> 00:22:08.994
Oh. yeah. he would...

406
00:22:08.995 --> 00:22:11.121
if you let me go.

407
00:22:12.707 --> 00:22:15.542
Get my ass shot for you?

408
00:22:15.543 --> 00:22:17.795
I don't think so.

409
00:22:19.797 --> 00:22:22.800
I think you 'bout
done with this.

410
00:22:27.638 --> 00:22:30.682
Oh. country. So smart.

411
00:22:39.233 --> 00:22:40.985
I spoke to my father.

412
00:22:42.236 --> 00:22:44.905
He said we can handle
Olympia any way we like.

413
00:22:44.906 --> 00:22:46.656
What the fuck does that mean?

414
00:22:46.657 --> 00:22:48.825
It means he doesn't
wanna deal with her.

415
00:22:48.826 --> 00:22:53.747
Well. maybe we leave it alone.

416
00:22:53.748 --> 00:22:56.291
It could be dangerous.
You don't know her.

417
00:22:56.292 --> 00:22:59.544
Mm. I know her better
than you. actually.

418
00:22:59.545 --> 00:23:04.549
Yeah. I knew her before
she married your dad.

419
00:23:04.550 --> 00:23:07.010
Oh. yeah? What was
she like back then?

420
00:23:07.011 --> 00:23:08.929
Whew. Ambitious.

421
00:23:08.930 --> 00:23:12.349
After your mom died. she. uh...

422
00:23:12.350 --> 00:23:15.143
She went after Chin like a
heat-seeking fucking missile.

423
00:23:15.144 --> 00:23:18.021
That makes sense.

424
00:23:18.022 --> 00:23:20.649
I remember when
she first moved in.

425
00:23:20.650 --> 00:23:24.277
I was 9. She brought me
this cute little teddy bear.

426
00:23:24.278 --> 00:23:27.030
In front of my dad. she acted
like the perfect mother.

427
00:23:27.031 --> 00:23:28.365
I could see it.

428
00:23:28.366 --> 00:23:30.617
She'd do anything to
get in good with Chin.

429
00:23:30.618 --> 00:23:32.869
Yeah. 'cause as soon
as he wasn't around.

430
00:23:32.870 --> 00:23:35.622
she'd scream at
me for no reason.

431
00:23:35.623 --> 00:23:37.624
One time I didn't eat my
vegetables or some shit.

432
00:23:37.625 --> 00:23:38.959
and she ripped off
my teddy bear's head

433
00:23:38.960 --> 00:23:40.961
and threw it in the garbage.

434
00:23:40.962 --> 00:23:42.629
You ever tell your
father about it?

435
00:23:42.630 --> 00:23:44.714
No. that just would
have made things worse.

436
00:23:44.715 --> 00:23:48.301
But I knew in that moment
I'd never love her.

437
00:23:48.302 --> 00:23:49.636
It's funny. these things
you feel as a kid.

438
00:23:49.637 --> 00:23:51.805
they stay with you.

439
00:23:51.806 --> 00:23:54.432
Yeah. but what are you gonna do?

440
00:23:54.433 --> 00:23:55.600
You know. shit happens.

441
00:23:55.601 --> 00:23:59.563
Yeah. It does.

442
00:23:59.564 --> 00:24:01.648
Still. I know she's
planning something.

443
00:24:01.649 --> 00:24:04.526
I'll keep my ears to the ground.

444
00:24:04.527 --> 00:24:07.028
Might need more than just your
ears with this fucking <i>puttana.</i>

445
00:24:11.742 --> 00:24:13.827
What do you like better?

446
00:24:13.828 --> 00:24:15.913
The grits or the ghetto
broad that serves 'em?

447
00:24:19.333 --> 00:24:20.500
Hey. porch monkey. no littering.

448
00:24:20.501 --> 00:24:22.169
Step off my dick. you pig!

449
00:24:22.170 --> 00:24:24.296
- What?
- You're under arrest.

450
00:24:24.297 --> 00:24:25.589
What the fuck. man?

451
00:24:25.590 --> 00:24:27.841
- He didn't do anything.
- What's going on?

452
00:24:27.842 --> 00:24:31.803
- Hey. what's going on here?
- Get the fuck back!

453
00:24:31.804 --> 00:24:34.055
We got plenty of room if
anybody else wants to come.

454
00:24:34.056 --> 00:24:36.308
What exactly is this
man being arrested for?

455
00:24:36.309 --> 00:24:39.686
Littering. loitering.
and harassing an officer.

456
00:24:39.687 --> 00:24:41.021
- Oh. hell. no.
- Let's go.

457
00:24:41.022 --> 00:24:42.772
Oh. come on.

458
00:24:45.484 --> 00:24:47.235
Racist pigs.

459
00:24:47.236 --> 00:24:49.070
You have no idea.

460
00:24:49.071 --> 00:24:51.615
- That's some bull.
- Guys ain't no good.

461
00:24:59.624 --> 00:25:01.542
Get
out of the fucking car.

462
00:25:10.968 --> 00:25:14.931
- What do you got?
- I need intel now.

463
00:25:17.225 --> 00:25:18.850
They took a vote.

464
00:25:18.851 --> 00:25:20.894
Gon' make a direct attack
on one of your pig mobiles.

465
00:25:20.895 --> 00:25:22.646
What does that mean. exactly?

466
00:25:22.647 --> 00:25:26.107
An empty cop car as
a symbolic gesture.

467
00:25:26.108 --> 00:25:27.692
Jesus Christ.

468
00:25:27.693 --> 00:25:30.403
Got no respect
for nothing. When?

469
00:25:30.404 --> 00:25:32.781
Ain't been planned
yet. Can I be done?

470
00:25:32.782 --> 00:25:34.282
You're done when
I say you're done.

471
00:25:34.283 --> 00:25:36.618
Go back. Tell 'em we gave
you a beatdown and let you go

472
00:25:36.619 --> 00:25:39.287
because we didn't feel
like doing the paperwork.

473
00:25:39.288 --> 00:25:42.540
They're suspicious
of infiltrators.

474
00:25:42.541 --> 00:25:43.708
Hope they believe it.

475
00:25:43.709 --> 00:25:46.379
They'll believe it.

476
00:25:55.888 --> 00:25:59.808
Here. Drink up. You
need all your strength.

477
00:26:04.313 --> 00:26:06.690
That's enough.

478
00:26:06.691 --> 00:26:08.483
Can you send Pettigrew
in to see me?

479
00:26:08.484 --> 00:26:10.902
You have to avoid stress.
I spoke to Nat Pettigrew.

480
00:26:10.903 --> 00:26:13.738
The men are out looking
for Chance right now.

481
00:26:13.739 --> 00:26:15.240
You don't understand.

482
00:26:15.241 --> 00:26:18.743
- I understand perfectly.
- Chance may be dead.

483
00:26:18.744 --> 00:26:20.370
And that's on me.

484
00:26:20.371 --> 00:26:24.165
Colombo's gonna make
a move. I know it.

485
00:26:24.166 --> 00:26:26.001
I got to figure out the plans.

486
00:26:26.002 --> 00:26:30.005
You have to think about
yourself and your family.

487
00:26:30.006 --> 00:26:33.008
Colombo's got me in check.
I got to figure a way out.

488
00:26:33.009 --> 00:26:35.552
Well. once you get better.
you will set things right.

489
00:26:35.553 --> 00:26:36.970
And in the meanwhile.

490
00:26:36.971 --> 00:26:39.848
I will give Nat any instructions
you have for him. okay?

491
00:26:39.849 --> 00:26:45.395
I tried to build something
without the Italians.

492
00:26:45.396 --> 00:26:47.605
Maybe it can't be done.

493
00:26:47.606 --> 00:26:51.860
Just please don't make
yourself upset over this.

494
00:26:51.861 --> 00:26:55.780
Ellsworth. if anything
happens to your heart.

495
00:26:55.781 --> 00:26:57.615
my heart goes with it.

496
00:26:57.616 --> 00:27:01.745
I might as well be laying here
in this hospital bed with you.

497
00:27:01.746 --> 00:27:04.831
I can't live without you. baby.

498
00:27:04.832 --> 00:27:08.168
You have to get better.

499
00:27:08.169 --> 00:27:10.712
I'll try.

500
00:27:10.713 --> 00:27:13.006
Well. then
close your eyes and rest.

501
00:27:13.007 --> 00:27:16.718
The doctor said that's
the best medicine.

502
00:27:16.719 --> 00:27:18.053
Sleep.

503
00:27:23.309 --> 00:27:24.643
Good.

504
00:27:34.945 --> 00:27:38.949
No man can be at
peace unless he has freedom.

505
00:27:47.833 --> 00:27:50.835
Am I dreaming?

506
00:27:50.836 --> 00:27:52.837
For any type of progress.

507
00:27:52.838 --> 00:27:55.006
We have to dream
as the first step.

508
00:27:55.007 --> 00:28:00.470
My best man. Chance...

509
00:28:00.471 --> 00:28:01.931
he may be dead.

510
00:28:03.808 --> 00:28:05.518
And that's on me.

511
00:28:07.895 --> 00:28:10.105
What should I do. man?

512
00:28:10.106 --> 00:28:12.857
I told you before. I can't
make choices for you.

513
00:28:12.858 --> 00:28:17.487
My desire for you was
to gain consciousness.

514
00:28:17.488 --> 00:28:19.489
I'm running out of time.

515
00:28:21.534 --> 00:28:23.493
What's so funny?

516
00:28:23.494 --> 00:28:25.912
Brother. you can't
gain consciousness

517
00:28:25.913 --> 00:28:29.332
until you know every
part of yourself.

518
00:28:29.333 --> 00:28:31.584
even the weak parts.

519
00:28:31.585 --> 00:28:34.879
It may be counterintuitive.
but fear pushes us

520
00:28:34.880 --> 00:28:39.175
to be more resilient
and compassionate.

521
00:28:39.176 --> 00:28:42.763
to clarify what's
truly important.

522
00:28:47.226 --> 00:28:49.061
Think on that for a while.

523
00:28:53.315 --> 00:28:55.401
You dozed off
there for a second.

524
00:29:04.994 --> 00:29:07.412
Did a good piece of work. kid.

525
00:29:07.413 --> 00:29:10.123
The message you had me sending
Bumpy almost got me killed.

526
00:29:10.124 --> 00:29:12.500
It's a risky business.

527
00:29:12.501 --> 00:29:14.169
Yeah. well. I don't get
paid enough for this shit.

528
00:29:14.170 --> 00:29:18.339
Oh. Frank. Frank.
Frank. now stick around.

529
00:29:18.340 --> 00:29:20.758
I got somethin' else for you.

530
00:29:20.759 --> 00:29:21.843
Pays better.

531
00:29:21.844 --> 00:29:25.346
I think you're gonna like it.

532
00:29:25.347 --> 00:29:27.348
I think you should
give it to Vinnie.

533
00:29:27.349 --> 00:29:29.601
He ain't doing shit
but standing back here.

534
00:29:29.602 --> 00:29:31.811
He look like he could
use a little work.

535
00:29:31.812 --> 00:29:34.731
Nah. this ain't a Vinnie job.

536
00:29:34.732 --> 00:29:36.816
You're smarter and more
capable than Vinnie.

537
00:29:36.817 --> 00:29:37.942
No offense.

538
00:29:37.943 --> 00:29:39.986
None taken.

539
00:29:39.987 --> 00:29:42.363
Pays $10.000.

540
00:29:42.364 --> 00:29:43.907
Sound good?

541
00:29:43.908 --> 00:29:45.868
To do what?

542
00:29:48.078 --> 00:29:50.164
Kill Bumpy Johnson.

543
00:29:53.125 --> 00:29:54.959
I don't know what
you put in this.

544
00:29:54.960 --> 00:29:57.253
but you a crazy motherfucker.

545
00:29:57.254 --> 00:30:00.089
Oh. he's in the hospital.
Shouldn't be too difficult.

546
00:30:00.090 --> 00:30:02.967
The motherfucker's
surrounded by guards.

547
00:30:02.968 --> 00:30:04.219
And probably gon'
die in there anyway.

548
00:30:04.220 --> 00:30:06.054
I wanna make sure he does.

549
00:30:06.055 --> 00:30:07.680
The real money's in junk.

550
00:30:07.681 --> 00:30:10.058
Bumpy made a deal
with the Genovese

551
00:30:10.059 --> 00:30:12.185
not to deal in Harlem.
That hurts us all.

552
00:30:12.186 --> 00:30:17.232
If he's gone. that
shit goes away.

553
00:30:17.233 --> 00:30:19.359
What about his lap dog. Chance?

554
00:30:19.360 --> 00:30:21.027
I'll give him a
shot to play ball.

555
00:30:21.028 --> 00:30:23.655
He could be useful.

556
00:30:23.656 --> 00:30:26.991
If not. I get rid
of him. I use you.

557
00:30:26.992 --> 00:30:29.369
- Use me?
- That's right.

558
00:30:29.370 --> 00:30:33.414
Yeah. I don't
know if that's possible.

559
00:30:33.415 --> 00:30:34.624
Oh. but it is.

560
00:30:34.625 --> 00:30:38.628
With the power of my
family behind you.

561
00:30:38.629 --> 00:30:42.675
Not bad for a country
boy off the bus. huh?

562
00:30:44.718 --> 00:30:46.678
I mean...

563
00:30:46.679 --> 00:30:49.430
I could do it.

564
00:30:49.431 --> 00:30:53.893
Somebody's gonna have to
take Bumpy Johnson's place.

565
00:30:53.894 --> 00:30:56.063
Might as well be you.

566
00:31:02.653 --> 00:31:04.946
I was surprised
to get your call.

567
00:31:04.947 --> 00:31:07.156
Thank you for seeing me. Tommy.

568
00:31:07.157 --> 00:31:10.285
Sit down. sit down. Okay?

569
00:31:10.286 --> 00:31:16.082
Sit down. I heard
you were in town.

570
00:31:16.083 --> 00:31:18.418
I just wanted to see
how you were doing.

571
00:31:18.419 --> 00:31:20.878
I didn't think you wanted to.

572
00:31:20.879 --> 00:31:23.131
Thought maybe. you know.

573
00:31:23.132 --> 00:31:25.883
you blamed me for what
happened to your hand.

574
00:31:25.884 --> 00:31:27.302
I don't blame you.

575
00:31:27.303 --> 00:31:29.929
It was your fucking lunatic
husband that did it.

576
00:31:29.930 --> 00:31:34.058
He was always jealous of us.
I mean. who could blame him?

577
00:31:34.059 --> 00:31:36.436
We had really good times
together. me and you.

578
00:31:36.437 --> 00:31:40.733
Lookit. I didn't ask
you here for that.

579
00:31:42.776 --> 00:31:45.486
I understand.

580
00:31:45.487 --> 00:31:47.947
Lookit. Olympia. what
happened between you and me

581
00:31:47.948 --> 00:31:51.159
can never fucking happen
again. do you understand?

582
00:31:51.160 --> 00:31:52.785
Sure.

583
00:31:52.786 --> 00:31:57.540
So. Olympia. what are
you doing back in town?

584
00:31:57.541 --> 00:32:00.960
Why am I here? I
belong here. Tommy.

585
00:32:00.961 --> 00:32:03.087
And it's time for
a little payback.

586
00:32:03.088 --> 00:32:07.091
You know me. I'm not
a malicious person.

587
00:32:07.092 --> 00:32:10.178
I've never held a
grudge in my life.

588
00:32:10.179 --> 00:32:13.139
But my stepdaughter. she's evil.

589
00:32:13.140 --> 00:32:15.767
She ran Vincent out of town.

590
00:32:15.768 --> 00:32:17.185
Next it'll be you.

591
00:32:17.186 --> 00:32:19.187
- Me?
- Of course.

592
00:32:19.188 --> 00:32:20.313
What do you think.
she doesn't resent you

593
00:32:20.314 --> 00:32:22.065
for trying to have her whacked?

594
00:32:22.066 --> 00:32:24.108
She's probably scheming

595
00:32:24.109 --> 00:32:26.527
with that Pino right
now to take you out.

596
00:32:26.528 --> 00:32:29.697
I don't know who the
fuck you're talking to.

597
00:32:29.698 --> 00:32:31.532
where you're coming
up with all this shit.

598
00:32:31.533 --> 00:32:36.162
I hear things. Tommy.
Okay? And I know her.

599
00:32:36.163 --> 00:32:37.830
And she needs to go.

600
00:32:37.831 --> 00:32:40.541
And this time for good.
Tommy. No mistakes.

601
00:32:40.542 --> 00:32:44.962
I'm not vindictive.
It's not for me.

602
00:32:44.963 --> 00:32:46.590
This is all for your sake.

603
00:32:52.596 --> 00:32:55.932
- Pigs don't scare me.
- Good.

604
00:32:55.933 --> 00:32:58.142
'Cause you know if we do this.
they're gon' crack down. right?

605
00:32:58.143 --> 00:32:59.977
I know.

606
00:32:59.978 --> 00:33:03.022
It's just it's important that
we're seen as a force of good

607
00:33:03.023 --> 00:33:04.941
in the community.
- Which we are.

608
00:33:04.942 --> 00:33:07.735
Start blowing things up.
that perception may change.

609
00:33:07.736 --> 00:33:10.822
Well. look. we're
defending ourselves

610
00:33:10.823 --> 00:33:13.574
against our oppressors.
just like in Vietnam.

611
00:33:13.575 --> 00:33:18.622
You saying you
believe in that war?

612
00:33:20.416 --> 00:33:22.625
You served over there.

613
00:33:22.626 --> 00:33:25.253
My son.

614
00:33:25.254 --> 00:33:28.339
- You got a son?
- Rodney.

615
00:33:28.340 --> 00:33:31.008
Just a kid. Shit. I was
a kid when I had him.

616
00:33:33.220 --> 00:33:36.264
No sooner turned 18.

617
00:33:36.265 --> 00:33:38.099
they swallowed him whole.

618
00:33:38.100 --> 00:33:40.184
chewed him up in basic training.

619
00:33:40.185 --> 00:33:42.019
spit him out into the Big Muddy.

620
00:33:42.020 --> 00:33:44.230
I didn't know.

621
00:33:44.231 --> 00:33:46.524
I don't like talking about it.

622
00:33:46.525 --> 00:33:48.026
Afraid I might jinx his life.

623
00:33:51.113 --> 00:33:52.448
Can I show you somethin'?

624
00:33:54.450 --> 00:33:56.075
My son sends me letters.

625
00:33:56.076 --> 00:33:58.036
but the government
reads 'em first.

626
00:34:02.958 --> 00:34:07.170
They worried he'll say
bad things about the Army.

627
00:34:07.171 --> 00:34:09.088
I can't believe this.

628
00:34:09.089 --> 00:34:11.466
The U.S. government spying
on our own soldiers.

629
00:34:11.467 --> 00:34:15.052
You must really miss him.

630
00:34:17.264 --> 00:34:19.223
- It's the pigs!
- What the fuck?

631
00:34:19.224 --> 00:34:21.434
- Against the wall! Move!
- This is messed up.

632
00:34:21.435 --> 00:34:24.145
Hands against the wall
where we can see 'em.

633
00:34:24.146 --> 00:34:26.230
- Against the wall!
- Hands down.

634
00:34:26.231 --> 00:34:28.483
All of youse. You
know the drill.

635
00:34:28.484 --> 00:34:31.944
Turn around. Face the wall.

636
00:34:31.945 --> 00:34:33.613
Take it easy.

637
00:34:33.614 --> 00:34:36.324
- Cut the mattresses.
- Hey! Go straight ahead.

638
00:34:36.325 --> 00:34:39.410
What are you doing?

639
00:34:39.411 --> 00:34:41.204
Turn out those drawers.

640
00:34:41.205 --> 00:34:44.624
There's no cameras.
Put the camera down.

641
00:34:44.625 --> 00:34:46.042
This is clean.
Not seeing anything.

642
00:34:46.043 --> 00:34:47.293
No. nothing here.

643
00:34:48.504 --> 00:34:49.879
Nothing?

644
00:34:49.880 --> 00:34:51.130
Nothing.

645
00:34:52.174 --> 00:34:53.424
All right.

646
00:34:57.846 --> 00:34:59.348
Get out!

647
00:35:00.891 --> 00:35:03.309
I'm guessing you didn't bother
getting yourself a warrant.

648
00:35:03.310 --> 00:35:07.356
Did you... Sergeant?

649
00:35:09.233 --> 00:35:10.316
Hey. hey!

650
00:35:10.317 --> 00:35:11.901
You son of a bitch!

651
00:35:11.902 --> 00:35:13.945
You goddamn animal!

652
00:35:15.906 --> 00:35:17.698
Confiscate the cameras.

653
00:35:17.699 --> 00:35:20.451
- Give it up.
- Give me the camera now.

654
00:35:20.452 --> 00:35:22.328
Hand it over.

655
00:35:22.329 --> 00:35:24.206
Now what
you think you doing?

656
00:35:26.792 --> 00:35:28.709
All right.
boys. let's go.

657
00:35:28.710 --> 00:35:31.087
There'll
be consequences.

658
00:35:42.224 --> 00:35:43.392
Are you okay?

659
00:36:09.376 --> 00:36:12.296
Hey. can I
get some help in here?

660
00:36:34.610 --> 00:36:37.821
Back the fuck away!

661
00:36:39.823 --> 00:36:40.740
Drop it.

662
00:36:40.741 --> 00:36:42.241
Kick it underneath the bed.

663
00:36:44.786 --> 00:36:47.413
I figured Colombo would
send your sorry ass.

664
00:36:47.414 --> 00:36:50.207
Chance... he still alive?

665
00:36:50.208 --> 00:36:51.584
Yeah. he alive. I swear.

666
00:36:51.585 --> 00:36:53.377
Might not be able to
say the same for you.

667
00:36:53.378 --> 00:36:55.588
Get on your knees.

668
00:36:55.589 --> 00:36:59.425
Don't tempt me. boy! Get
on your fucking knees!

669
00:36:59.426 --> 00:37:01.761
I know you ain't got no God.

670
00:37:01.762 --> 00:37:03.971
So. say goodbye to
your mama and your kid.

671
00:37:03.972 --> 00:37:06.057
'Cause you gon' see
them in the next life.

672
00:37:06.058 --> 00:37:08.267
Spare me. Teach me like you did
Chance when you first met him.

673
00:37:08.268 --> 00:37:10.269
You ain't half the
man that Chance is.

674
00:37:10.270 --> 00:37:11.812
You never will be.

675
00:37:11.813 --> 00:37:14.650
You done tested me
one too many times.

676
00:37:16.568 --> 00:37:21.197
Mama watching over me. I
need your strength right now.

677
00:37:21.198 --> 00:37:23.449
I know I done let you down.

678
00:37:23.450 --> 00:37:26.494
I know this ain't
what we talked about.

679
00:37:26.495 --> 00:37:28.747
I'm sorry.

680
00:37:29.957 --> 00:37:34.043
The real enemy
is not our fellow Black man.

681
00:37:34.044 --> 00:37:37.630
but the system that pits
us against each other.

682
00:37:37.631 --> 00:37:41.551
This motherfucker came in
here and tried to kill me.

683
00:37:44.429 --> 00:37:48.391
We must stop turning our
guns against each other

684
00:37:48.392 --> 00:37:53.646
and recognize who the
true oppressor is.

685
00:38:04.282 --> 00:38:06.117
Malcolm.

686
00:38:12.207 --> 00:38:13.833
Get up.

687
00:38:16.294 --> 00:38:17.753
Get out.

688
00:38:17.754 --> 00:38:20.881
Tell Colombo I want to see
his sorry white ass down here.

689
00:38:20.882 --> 00:38:22.968
We'll make a deal for Chance.

690
00:38:38.984 --> 00:38:42.570
Look. I did what
you guys asked me.

691
00:38:42.571 --> 00:38:45.322
I invited Olympia
to break bread.

692
00:38:45.323 --> 00:38:48.409
I met with her. I wanted to
see what was on her mind.

693
00:38:48.410 --> 00:38:49.952
And?

694
00:38:49.953 --> 00:38:52.872
Well. just like you predicted.

695
00:38:52.873 --> 00:38:56.292
she said <i>you</i> wanted to whack me.

696
00:38:56.293 --> 00:38:58.169
Tommy. you swear on this?

697
00:38:58.170 --> 00:39:01.130
I don't want any trouble
between the families.

698
00:39:01.131 --> 00:39:03.132
All right. then.
the answer is clear.

699
00:39:03.133 --> 00:39:05.926
It really breaks my
heart to say this.

700
00:39:05.927 --> 00:39:10.139
because I still have
feelings for her.

701
00:39:10.140 --> 00:39:11.433
But she's gotta go.

702
00:39:13.810 --> 00:39:17.146
You father left it up to us.

703
00:39:17.147 --> 00:39:19.523
No.

704
00:39:19.524 --> 00:39:22.443
Stella. Tommy's not the
only boss she knows.

705
00:39:22.444 --> 00:39:24.487
She could cause
a lot of trouble.

706
00:39:24.488 --> 00:39:25.946
She has dirt on me.

707
00:39:25.947 --> 00:39:28.365
the Gambinos. and
God knows what else.

708
00:39:28.366 --> 00:39:30.117
She could hurt a lot of people.

709
00:39:30.118 --> 00:39:34.538
If she were a man. this would
be a no-fucking-brainer.

710
00:39:34.539 --> 00:39:38.751
Stella. I say we got to do it.

711
00:39:38.752 --> 00:39:44.173
No. That's not what I want.

712
00:39:44.174 --> 00:39:48.135
I want to scare the
fucking shit out of her.

713
00:39:48.136 --> 00:39:51.514
And how are you going
to do that. Stella?

714
00:39:51.515 --> 00:39:54.308
Tell her you followed through
on everything that she asked.

715
00:39:54.309 --> 00:39:56.769
that you killed me.
and then send her a car

716
00:39:56.770 --> 00:39:59.439
to take her to the farm
to see my dead body.

717
00:40:00.607 --> 00:40:02.233
Then what?

718
00:40:02.234 --> 00:40:05.987
Just leave the rest to me.

719
00:40:11.993 --> 00:40:13.744
It's a good thing
we moved the dynamite

720
00:40:13.745 --> 00:40:15.788
out of here to a
secure location.

721
00:40:15.789 --> 00:40:17.832
In the nick of time.
too. That was close.

722
00:40:17.833 --> 00:40:22.503
The question is. who told
them pigs to come looking?

723
00:40:22.504 --> 00:40:24.797
- Hmm.
- You saying we got a rat?

724
00:40:24.798 --> 00:40:26.173
No doubt about it.

725
00:40:26.174 --> 00:40:28.467
The minute we moved
the explosives in.

726
00:40:28.468 --> 00:40:30.386
everybody in this place knew.

727
00:40:30.387 --> 00:40:32.555
It could be any one of us.

728
00:40:32.556 --> 00:40:34.390
Shoot. it could be somebody
sitting at this table right now.

729
00:40:34.391 --> 00:40:39.812
Might be me. If I was
the one that told Dolan.

730
00:40:39.813 --> 00:40:42.149
would be smart to get him
to punch me in the face.

731
00:40:45.485 --> 00:40:48.529
- That is conviction. girl.
- Come on. now.

732
00:40:48.530 --> 00:40:52.449
Whoever it is. I think I
know how to smoke 'em out.

733
00:40:52.450 --> 00:40:54.034
How?

734
00:40:54.035 --> 00:40:57.663
I'm gonna put myself
in my father's shoes.

735
00:40:57.664 --> 00:41:02.334
Ask myself. what would
Bumpy Johnson do?

736
00:41:24.816 --> 00:41:26.609
Looking
good. Mrs. Gigante.

737
00:41:26.610 --> 00:41:28.569
Thank you.

738
00:41:28.570 --> 00:41:31.155
What's your name. kid?

739
00:41:31.156 --> 00:41:35.034
Anthony.

740
00:41:35.035 --> 00:41:37.494
How would you like to
be my personal driver

741
00:41:37.495 --> 00:41:38.913
from now on. Anthony?

742
00:41:38.914 --> 00:41:40.831
I'd like that a lot.

743
00:41:40.832 --> 00:41:42.750
Done.

744
00:41:42.751 --> 00:41:45.544
How much longer till
we get to the farm?

745
00:41:45.545 --> 00:41:46.922
Oh. about...

746
00:41:48.465 --> 00:41:53.385
Ohh!

747
00:42:02.771 --> 00:42:06.690
You fucking traitor!
You fucking traitor!

748
00:42:06.691 --> 00:42:08.734
- I'm gonna tell Vincent!
- Oh. yeah?

749
00:42:08.735 --> 00:42:10.110
Vincent said you're a dead man!

750
00:42:10.111 --> 00:42:11.904
Who the fuck do you
think approved this?

751
00:42:11.905 --> 00:42:14.740
This is a one-time message
from Stella Gigante.

752
00:42:14.741 --> 00:42:16.659
Stay the fuck out of
Harlem. you hear me?

753
00:42:16.660 --> 00:42:19.954
